1. A device comprising:
a diode laser (101) emitting a laser beam;
a splitter (102) which separates the laser beam;
an inline fiber isolator (105) and a tapered semiconductor optical amplifier (106) which receives a portion of the laser beam;
at least one pair of axicon prisms (108) which receives and creates an annular laser beam; and
a telescope (110) containing an inner portion through which the laser beam is transmitted.

2. The device of claim 1 further comprising:
an outer portion of the telescope to receive reflected laser light;
an interference filter (113) to receive the reflected laser light and filter the reflected laser light;
a narrow band etalon to receive the filtered reflected laser light and reduce background light;
a beam splitter (114) for splitting the reduced background light into a first portion and a second portion;
a total detection channel which receives at least one of the first portion of the reduced background light and the combined molecular collected backscatter and the aerosol and cloud collected backscatter;
a heated rubidium vapor cell (115) which receives the second portion of the reduced background light and blocks a spectrally narrow cloud and aerosol collected backscatter and passes wings of molecular collected backscatter; and
a molecular channel detector (116) for receiving the wings of molecular signal.

8. A method of analysis comprising:
generating a laser beam;
splitting a laser beam into a first portion and a second portions;
generating high energy pulses from the first portion of the laser beam;
expanding the first portion of the laser beam;
transmitting the expanded portion of the laser beam;
reflecting the transmitted laser beam;
receiving the reflected laser beam; and
analyzing the reflected laser beam.

16. A device comprising:
a laser (101) emitting a laser beam;
a splitter (102) which separates the laser (101) beam;
an amplifier which receives a portion of the laser (101) beam;
prisms (108) which receives and expands the laser (101) beam; and
a telescope (110) which transmits the laser beam.

17. The device of claim 16 further comprising:
a device which receives reflected laser light;
a filter (113) to receive the reflected laser light;
an etalon for receiving the filtered reflected laser light; and
a device for analyzing (116) the filtered reflected laser light.
